## Build Architecture (Single Bundle)

**Constraint**: npm package size must not increase.

### Current state
```
npm package:
  dist/bin.cjs     ← esbuild bundles src/bin.ts (CLI-only)

bun compile:
  dist-bin/sentry-*  ← Bun.build bundles src/bin.ts (native binary)
```

### New state
```
npm package:
  dist/index.cjs   ← esbuild bundles src/index.ts (library + CLI internals)
  dist/bin.cjs     ← tiny ~200 byte wrapper: shebang + require('./index.cjs')._cli()
  dist/index.d.cts ← type declarations (~30 lines)

bun compile:
  dist-bin/sentry-*  ← Bun.build bundles src/bin.ts (unchanged pipeline)
```

**Size impact**: `dist/index.cjs` replaces the old `dist/bin.cjs` — same code, same size (the library entry adds ~100 lines of source, negligible after minification). The tiny bin wrapper + type declarations add ~2 KB total.

**Sourcemaps**: Each build (esbuild and Bun.build) gets its own debug ID via `injectDebugId`. Both sourcemaps are uploaded to Sentry. Debug IDs handle deduplication — frames from the Node.js bundle match one sourcemap, frames from the Bun binary match the other.

### Source file changes

Extract CLI runner from `bin.ts` so both entry points share it:

```
src/
├── index.ts     ← NEW: library API + re-exports _cli (esbuild entry for npm)
├── cli.ts       ← NEW: extracted CLI runner (dispatch, middleware, telemetry)
├── bin.ts       ← SIMPLIFIED: thin wrapper, imports/calls cli.ts (bun compile entry)
├── app.ts       # unchanged
├── context.ts   # unchanged
└── lib/         # unchanged (except env.ts + process.env ports)
```

**`src/cli.ts`** — Extracted CLI runner. Contains the completion fast-path, full CLI runner with middleware (auto-auth, seer trial), and the dispatch logic. Exported as functions, no top-level execution.

**`src/bin.ts`** — Simplified to ~15 lines. Sets up stream error handlers (EPIPE/EIO), imports `startCli()` from `cli.ts`, calls it. Only used by `bun compile`.

**`src/index.ts`** — Library entry point. Exports `sentry()` (default + named), `SentryError`, `SentryOptions`. Also exports `_cli` from `cli.ts` for the npm bin wrapper.

